00:10:51.560 --> 00:10:51.700
But

179
00:10:52.820 --> 00:10:55.220
really, let's ground the conversation in genome instability.

180
00:10:55.320 --> 00:10:58.980
So genome instability acts as both an enabler and a vulnerability in

181
00:10:59.080 --> 00:11:01.260
cancer. So what do I mean by genome instability?

182
00:11:01.720 --> 00:11:05.560
Really, it's the propensity of cells to continuously accumulate more and more

183
00:11:05.580 --> 00:11:09.560
mutations. And when this occurs, this can be a benefit to

184
00:11:09.620 --> 00:11:13.360
cancer development and progression in the sense that it provides

185
00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:17.580
enough genomic diversity for cancer cells to use

186
00:11:17.620 --> 00:11:21.440
in terms of adaptations, selection, and also expansion.

187
00:11:21.480 --> 00:11:25.150
Just giving a little example of how that can happen in terms of hypoxia on the

188
00:11:25.200 --> 00:11:29.100
left-hand side. But also important to remember that DNA damage

189
00:11:29.140 --> 00:11:32.680
itself or genome instability, I should say, can be a vulnerability with

190
00:11:33.040 --> 00:11:36.320
cancer as well, and where certain drugs, such as platinum, will

191
00:11:36.400 --> 00:11:38.580
actually increase DNA damage further,

192
00:11:39.480 --> 00:11:43.160
hoping to overwhelm cancer cells with too much DNA damage that they can't just

193
00:11:43.200 --> 00:11:46.940
possibly survive, or other drugs, such as PARP inhibitors that

194
00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:50.560
are meant to prevent DNA repair, but the same concept to try to overwhelm the

195
00:11:50.600 --> 00:11:50.920
cells.

196
00:11:52.100 --> 00:11:55.760
So looking for genome instability and recognizing these various patterns is quite

197
00:11:55.780 --> 00:11:59.520
important. And this is where the newly released TCGA data

198
00:11:59.580 --> 00:12:02.940
really does become important. So I won't highlight all of these points.

199
00:12:03.460 --> 00:12:06.160
Gad, I think covered that. I think I have 90X here. I would actually trust Gad.

